<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-23-0598 </DOCNO><TEXT>In May 1986 the new 'Integral Program for Wind Energy' (IPW) for the years1986-1990 was published. It includes opportunities for both investmentand development subsidies. The mechanism of the plan is explained. Nextto this IPW a new (the third) research program has been started, namedNOW-3. The main lines of the program are discussed. The Netherlands EnergyResearch Foundation's part in these programs is outlined. IN spite ofsome flaws in the regulation that had to be handled, the IPW is expectedto be an essential tool for stimulating the market and to reach the longterm goals for wind energy application in the Netherlands.</TEXT></DOC>